{"type":"message","id":"b4687595","parentId":"d2206293","timestamp":"2026-03-28T11:59:55.843Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7SHGc3pVC0K2irbjP4Myjlc2|fc_075abb85efaf918e0169c7c2bad168819abf7d39b90719743f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ACTIVE_TASK_TEMPLATE.md\n\nStatus: active\nPriority: P1\nStarted: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM\nUpdated: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM\nWorkspace: /absolute/path\nOwner: main-session\nUser Trigger: original user instruction\nResume Entry: first file/report/command to reopen\n\n## Goal\n- One-sentence definition of the task to finish\n\n## Acceptance\n- Deliverable or proof 1\n- Deliverable or proof 2\n\n## Current\n- Exactly one item being executed now\n\n## Next\n- Next pending item\n- Next pending item after that\n\n## Completed\n- [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] Finished item + proof\n\n## Evidence\n- /absolute/path/to/file\n- command + key output summary\n\n## Blockers\n- None\n\n## Rules\n- `Current` must contain exactly one active item.\n- After finishing `Current`, move it to `Completed`, add proof under `Evidence`, then promote the first item in `Next` into `Current`.\n- Prefer rewriting the whole file once instead of chaining multiple partial edits.\n- After each write, read the file back and verify `Current`, `Next`, and `Completed` before reporting the new state.\n- If prompt context reports `Integrity Warnings`, repair the file before claiming the task state changed.\n- Only set `Status: blocked` when the blocker is real and specific.\n- Only set `Status: done` when `Acceptance` is met.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774699195834}}
