{"type":"message","id":"0f6e62c0","parentId":"682f059a","timestamp":"2026-03-28T12:21:25.507Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring song lyrics recovery**\n\nI see the title refers to a school song video, which probably has scrolling lyrics or subtitles. I could recover the full lyrics by applying repeated OCR across the frames—this could bypass ASR. I might use the Vision framework in Swift on my Mac to handle this. First, I'll need to extract some frames using AVFoundation and see if I can use it in a script. Capturing frames at intervals could work well for OCR later!\n\n**Planning subtitle extraction**\n\nI think the first step is to get subtitles through OCR. I could extract a frame every 5 seconds and then inspect them. The tool I’m considering can read images as attachments, which is great! I’ll need to save several frames for analysis. I’m thinking of writing a Swift script to capture frames every 10 seconds, aiming for around 17 frames. This could help in getting the subtitles sorted out efficiently!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_075abb85efaf918e0169c7c7b2c8e0819ab6a79326edbf734e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpx8e-Er3PesJJUFcE803KNKalbxmZk7cbgfIIJusAMjjDCqtO0kePGM-GNO0_ZUt8vQnTAN3OyPJlWFVsoDrmsFm1zPmNeGcOQ2uGsmltfWND1y5RfhUCG-6WyKQyuVtJWAjNNfqgIbqrNLIFWT2syCjZKMcV_ZT5QSX0c8La7y1wVHlMCkcZ4Fe4vXtOJrEG6XIoyIfIpziO4lLWvxx2EQ-CLOVhn5f2IJPpS92K0Gi9ftboi8iYzF0Y2dv-4RZcE5GJ3-e3n2Jd0C9Vq5hN_zq_XJks72YvTb9-MRO5x6AMBPdck6hNetRVo9EkY81s1rM8uqxNd4vhhuWbRR1DUKBFDROTuhh-8nJSrmFAs8xsJ0Xjcewq6eXQw1lPfIyMnY4RqGBpkv_5BcI6lWV6kW6O4bdD7yhJNCuIHIv2M4rGuk53FwgPmVsBbmxATJm4aN8u9f6HZIY4cWwHtRvCShppCzCCcQgUxYKOUSRpzAGkQexXBxBkTyhjDM47PR6neLEhnWpv0hiZBp5qLi6EeREathd03GfXToZqsjPeyCajVVq6xaxRsAfCK7j6zbh8uEnP4whMkSKS0DZp1V10DVfWJmAY7asU15omr_2OMLnTTKx7_4qRfART6b25FXKMlcohi4V-bcnOZBXLXIGc6HzdJqd_BcVECh5byhnEBpQr5boGHQ0QcC2P73QMmvRiwgp94GsPCIqEpaTzk8TXZ6O9GwgoUUM7XJ7ayigBYjL7WkKIzp3d8sHQG4tJIL46mHNRriGO8xx2vCl2a