id 0;\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/notify-8Hsm6NPW.js:59:\t\t\taccountId,\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/notify-8Hsm6NPW.js:95:\t\tsubscriber.accountId ?? \"\",\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/notify-8Hsm6NPW.js:104:\t\t...ctx.accountId ? { accountId: ctx.accountId } : {},\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/notify-8Hsm6NPW.js:162:\t\t\t...params.subscriber.accountId ? { accountId: params.subscriber.accountId } : {},\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/provider-onboard-CSnPvkMM.js:22:\tconst baseUrl = params?.accountId && params?.gatewayId ? resolveCloudflareAiGatewayBaseUrl({\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/provider-onboard-CSnPvkMM.js:23:\t\taccountId: params.accountId,"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":126,"aggregated":"/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:90:- Plugins/Matrix: stop mention-gated or otherwise dropped room chatter from refreshing focused thread bindings before the message is actually routed, so idle ACP and session bindings can still expire normally in mention-required rooms. Thanks @vincentkoc, @dinakars777 and @mvanhorn.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:344:- ACP/configured bindings: reinitialize configured ACP sessions that are stuck in `error` state instead of reusing the failed runtime.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:358:- Telegram/routing: fail loud when `message send` targets an unknown non-default Telegram `accountId`, instead of silently falling back to the channel-level bot token and sending through the wrong bot. (#50853) Thanks @hclsys.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:690:- Protocol/Swift model sync: regenerate pending node work Swift bindings after the landed `node.pending.*` schema additions so generated protocol artifacts are consistent again. (#41477) Thanks @mbelinky.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:751:- Matrix/DM routing: add safer fallback detection for broken `m.direct` homeservers, honor explicit room bindings over DM classification, and preserve room-bound agent selection for Matrix DM rooms. (#19736) Thanks @derbronko.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:812:- ACP/persistent channel bindings: add durable Discord channel and Telegram topic binding storage, routing resolution, and CLI/docs support so ACP thread targets survive restarts and can be managed consistently. (#34873) Thanks @dutifulbob.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:813:- Telegram/ACP topic bindings: accept Telegram Mac Unicode dash option prefixes in `/acp spawn`, support Telegram topic thread binding (`--thread here|auto`), route bound-topic follow-ups to ACP sessions, add actionable Telegram approval buttons with prefixed approval-id resolution, and pin successful bind confirmations in-topic. (#36683) Thanks @huntharo.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:814:- Telegram/topic agent routing: support per-topic `agentId` overrides in forum groups and DM topics so topics can route to dedicated agents with isolated sessions. (#33647; based on #31513) Thanks @kesor and @Sid-Qin.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:881:- Routing/binding lookup scalability: pre-index route bindings by channel/account and avoid full binding-list rescans on channel-account cache rollover, preventing multi-second `resolveAgentRoute` stalls in large binding configurations. (#36915) Thanks @songchenghao.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:929:- Slack/system-event session routing: resolve reaction/member/pin/interaction system-event session keys through channel/account bindings (with sender-aware DM routing) so inbound Slack events target the correct agent session in multi-account setups instead of defaulting to `agent:main`. (#34045) Thanks @paulomcg, @daht-mad and @vincentkoc.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:942:- ACP/Discord startup hardening: clean up stuck ACP worker children on gateway restart, unbind stale ACP thread bindings during Discord startup reconciliation, and add per-thread listener watchdog timeouts so wedged turns cannot block later messages. (#33699) Thanks @dutifulbob.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1077:- Telegram/native topic command routing: resolve forum-topic native commands through the same conversation route as inbound messages so topic `agentId` overrides and bound topic sessions target the active session instead of the default topic-parent session. (#38871) Thanks @obviyus.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1148:- Discord/native slash session fallback: treat empty configured bound-session keys as missing so `/status` and other native commands fall back to the routed slash session and routed channel session instead of blanking Discord session keys in normal channel bindings.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1330:- Feishu/default account resolution: always honor explicit `channels.feishu.defaultAccount` during outbound account selection (including top-level-credential setups where the preferred id is not present in `accounts`), instead of silently falling back to another account id. (#32253) Thanks @bmendonca3.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1346:- Pairing/AllowFrom account fallback: handle omitted `accountId` values in `readChannelAllowFromStore` and `readChannelAllowFromStoreSync` as `default`, while preserving legacy unscoped allowFrom merges for default-account flows. Thanks @Sid-Qin and @vincentkoc.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1352:- Agents/Subagents `sessions_spawn`: reject malformed `agentId` inputs before normalization (for example error-message/path-like strings) to prevent unintended synthetic agent IDs and ghost workspace/session paths; includes strict validation regression coverage. (#31381) Thanks @openperf.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1358:- Hooks/after_tool_call: include embedded session context (`sessionKey`, `agentId`) and fire the hook exactly once per tool execution by removing duplicate adapter-path dispatch in embedded runs. (#32201) Thanks @jbeno, @scoootscooob, @vincentkoc.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1397:- Discord/Thread bindings: replace fixed TTL lifecycle with inactivity (`idleHours`, default 24h) plus optional hard `maxAgeHours` lifecycle controls, and add `/session idle` + `/session max-age` commands for focused thread-bound sessions. (#27845) Thanks @osolmaz.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1406:- Feishu/Chat tooling: add `feishu_chat` tool actions for chat info and member queries, with configurable enablement under `channels.feishu.tools.chat`. (#14674) Thanks @liuweifly.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1429:- Agents/Sessions list transcript paths: handle missing/non-string/relative `sessions.list.path` values and per-agent `{agentId}` templates when deriving `transcriptPath`, so cross-agent session listings resolve to concrete agent session files instead of workspace-relative paths. (#24775) Thanks @martinfrancois.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1452:- Slack/Announce target account routing: enable session-backed announce-target lookup for Slack so multi-account announces resolve the correct `accountId` instead of defaulting to bot-token context. Landed from contributor PR #31028 by @taw0002. Thanks @taw0002.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1467:- Feishu/Group wildcard policy fallback: honor `channels.feishu.groups[\"*\"]` when no explicit group match exists so unmatched groups inherit wildcard reply-policy settings instead of falling back to global defaults. (#29456) Thanks @WaynePika.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1473:- Feishu/Multi-account + reply reliability: add `channels.feishu.defaultAccount` outbound routing support with schema validation, keep quoted-message extraction text-first (post/interactive/file placeholders instead of raw JSON), route Feishu video sends as `msg_type: \"file\"`, and avoid websocket event blocking by using non-blocking event handling in monitor dispatch. Landed from contributor PRs #29610, #30432, #30331, and #29501. Thanks @hclsys, @bmendonca3, @patrick-yingxi-pan, and @zwffff.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1485:- Feishu/Reaction notifications: add `channels.feishu.reactionNotifications` (`off | own | all`, default `own`) so operators can disable reaction ingress or allow all verified reaction events (not only bot-authored message reactions). (#28529) Thanks @cowboy129.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1488:- Feishu/Group sender allowlist fallback: add global `channels.feishu.groupSenderAllowFrom` sender authorization for group chats, with per-group `groups.<id>.allowFrom` precedence and regression coverage for allow/block/precedence behavior. (#29174) Thanks @1MoreBuild.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1533:- Security/Subagents sandbox inheritance: block sandboxed sessions from spawning cross-agent subagents that would run unsandboxed, preventing runtime sandbox downgrade via `sessions_spawn agentId`. Thanks @tdjackey for reporting.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1561:- Feishu/Multi-account + reply reliability: add `channels.feishu.defaultAccount` outbound routing support with schema validation, prevent inbound preview text from leaking into prompt system events, keep quoted-message extraction text-first (post/interactive/file placeholders instead of raw JSON), route Feishu video sends as `msg_type: \"file\"`, and avoid websocket event blocking by using non-blocking event handling in monitor dispatch. Landed from contributor PRs #31209, #29610, #30432, #30331, and #29501. Thanks @stakeswky, @hclsys, @bmendonca3, @patrick-yingxi-pan, and @zwffff.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1562:- Feishu/Target routing + replies + dedupe: normalize provider-prefixed targets (`feishu:`/`lark:`), prefer configured `channels.feishu.defaultAccount` for tool execution, honor Feishu outbound `renderMode` in adapter text/caption sends, fall back to normal send when reply targets are withdrawn/deleted, and add synchronous in-memory dedupe guard for concurrent duplicate inbound events. Landed from contributor PRs #30428, #30438, #29958, #30444, and #29463. Thanks @bmendonca3 and @Yaxuan42.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1563:- Channels/Multi-account default routing: add optional `channels.<channel>.defaultAccount` default-selection support across message channels so omitted `accountId` routes to an explicit configured account instead of relying on implicit first-entry ordering (fallback behavior unchanged when unset).\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1564:- Telegram/Multi-account fallback isolation: fail closed for non-default Telegram accounts when route resolution falls back to `matchedBy=default`, preventing cross-account DM/session contamination without explicit account bindings. (#31110)\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1583:- Routing/Binding peer-kind parity: treat `peer.kind` `group` and `channel` as equivalent for binding scope matching (while keeping `direct` separate) so Slack/public channel bindings do not silently fall through. Landed from contributor PR #31135. Thanks @Sid-Qin.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1606:- Cron/Failure delivery routing: add `failureAlert.mode` (`announce|webhook`) and `failureAlert.accountId` support, plus `cron.failureDestination` and per-job `delivery.failureDestination` routing with duplicate-target suppression, best-effort skip behavior, and global+job merge semantics. Landed from contributor PR #31059. Thanks @kesor.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1617:- Cron/Session target guardrail: reject creating or patching `sessionTarget: \"main\"` cron jobs when `agentId` is not the default agent, preventing invalid cross-agent main-session bindings at write time. (#30217) Thanks @liaosvcaf.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1683:- Agents/Routing CLI: add `openclaw agents bindings`, `openclaw agents bind`, and `openclaw agents unbind` for account-scoped route management, including channel-only to account-scoped binding upgrades, role-aware binding identity handling, plugin-resolved binding account IDs, and optional account-binding prompts in `openclaw channels add`. (#27195) thanks @gumadeiras.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1733:- Feishu/Doc tools: route `feishu_doc` and `feishu_app_scopes` through the active agent account context (with explicit `accountId` override support) so multi-account agents no longer default to the first configured app, with regression coverage for context routing and explicit override behavior. (#27338) thanks @AaronL725.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1755:- Security/Node exec approvals: require structured `commandArgv` approvals for `host=node`, enforce `systemRunBinding` matching for argv/cwd/session/agent/env context with fail-closed behavior on missing/mismatched bindings, and add `GIT_EXTERNAL_DIFF` to blocked host env keys. This ships in the next npm release (`2026.2.26`). Thanks @tdjackey for reporting.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1762:- Security/Node exec approvals hardening: freeze immutable approval-time execution plans (`argv`/`cwd`/`agentId`/`sessionKey`) via `system.run.prepare`, enforce those canonical plan values during approval forwarding/execution, and reject mutable parent-symlink cwd paths during approval-plan building to prevent approval bypass via symlink rebind. This ships in the next npm release (`2026.2.26`). Thanks @tdjackey for reporting.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1801:- Cron/Message multi-account routing: honor explicit `delivery.accountId` for isolated cron delivery resolution, and when `message.send` omits `accountId`, fall back to the sending agent's bound channel account instead of defaulting to the global account. (#27015, #26975) Thanks @lbo728 and @stakeswky.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1802:- Gateway/Message media roots: thread `agentId` through gateway `send` RPC and prefer explicit `agentId` over session/default resolution so non-default agent workspace media sends no longer fail with `LocalMediaAccessError`; added regression coverage for agent precedence and blank-agent fallback. (#23249) Thanks @Sid-Qin.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:1819:- Agents/Model fallback: keep explicit text + image fallback chains reachable even when `agents.defaults.models` allowlists are present, prefer explicit run `agentId` over session-key parsing for followup fallback override resolution (with session-key fallback), treat agent-level fallback overrides as configured in embedded runner preflight, and classify `model_cooldown` / `cooling down` errors as `rate_limit` so failover continues. (#11972, #24137, #17231)\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2124:- Feishu/Commands: in group chats, command authorization now falls back to top-level `channels.feishu.allowFrom` when per-group `allowFrom` is not set, so `/command` no longer gets blocked by an unintended empty allowlist. (#23756) Thanks @steipete.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2198:- Memory/QMD: migrate legacy unscoped collection bindings (for example `memory-root`) to per-agent scoped names (for example `memory-root-main`) during startup when safe, so QMD-backed `memory_search` no longer fails with `Collection not found` after upgrades. (#23228, #20727) Thanks @JLDynamics and @AaronFaby.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2248:- Security/Control UI avatars: harden `/avatar/:agentId` local avatar serving by rejecting symlink paths and requiring fd-level file identity + size checks before reads. Thanks @tdjackey for reporting.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2260:- Config/Bindings: allow optional `bindings[].comment` in strict config validation so annotated binding entries no longer fail load. (#23458) Thanks @echoVic.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2599:- Cron: resolve `accountId` from agent bindings in isolated sessions. (#17996) Thanks @simonemacario.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2859:- Media/Security: allow outbound local media reads from the active agent workspace (including `workspace-<agentId>`) via agent-scoped local roots, avoiding broad global allowlisting of all per-agent workspaces. (#17136) Thanks @MisterGuy420.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2860:- Outbound/Media: thread explicit `agentId` through core `sendMessage` direct-delivery path so agent-scoped local media roots apply even when mirror metadata is absent. (#17268) Thanks @gumadeiras.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2968:- Sessions/Agents: pass `agentId` when resolving existing transcript paths in reply runs so non-default agents and heartbeat/chat handlers no longer fail with `Session file path must be within sessions directory`. (#15141) Thanks @Goldenmonstew.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2969:- Sessions/Agents: pass `agentId` through status and usage transcript-resolution paths (auto-reply, gateway usage APIs, and session cost/log loaders) so non-default agents can resolve absolute session files without path-validation failures. (#15103) Thanks @jalehman.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:2995:- Routing: enforce strict binding-scope matching across peer/guild/team/roles so peer-scoped Discord/Slack bindings no longer match unrelated guild/team contexts or fallback tiers. (#15274) Thanks @lailoo.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:3060:- Cron: use requested `agentId` for isolated job auth resolution. (#13983) Thanks @0xRaini.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:3062:- Cron: pass `agentId` to `runHeartbeatOnce` for main-session jobs. (#14140) Thanks @ishikawa-pro.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:3143:- Hooks: route webhook agent runs to specific `agentId`s, add `hooks.allowedAgentIds` controls, and fall back to default agent when unknown IDs are provided. (#13672) Thanks @BillChirico.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:3188:- Routing: refresh bindings per message by loading config at route resolution so binding changes apply without restart. (#11372) Thanks @juanpablodlc.\n/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/CHANGELOG.md:3276:- Telegram: pass `parentPeer` for forum topic binding inheritance so group-level b