_text\",\"text\":\"**Acknowledging user consent**\\n\\nI need to respond to the user who said \\\"好,\\\" which likely means they consent to cleaning. I should verify if there's an active task related to this or if I need to create or update an ACTIVE_TASK. Since this feels like a continuation of the same configuration task, it seems appropriate to treat it as a multi-step task. I might also need to check any checklists or previous ACTIVE_TASKs to confirm the status before proceeding with the new request.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering configuration tasks**\\n\\nI need to commit changes after any edits, but I’m not sure if a memory search is necessary since this is more about the current context than prior memory. I should check if I need to scan my skills and possibly open the openclaw-workspace to maintain workspace settings, though the config file is separate. There might not be a clear skill needed here. I will execute tool calls and inspect bindings and account settings, updating the openclaw.json if needed while being cautious about binding changes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting session configurations**\\n\\nI need to check the documentation or changelog for information on bound sessions. It seems the direct DM session key may remain active, which could mean new messages route to that existing session due to session persistence. If the session key comes from agent binding, it might open a new xiaoguanjia session. I should consider validating this by listing sessions after the next user message, although I can't do that right now. Maybe I should clean up the \\\"main residual route\\\" by unbinding if needed, and I need to understand how the default account affects the routes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating channel accounts**\\n\\nI'm looking into the current channel accounts, like main, feishu-assistant, and coding-agent. If the user prefers the account linked to xiaoguanjia over main, that could work. Since the user agreed to clean up residual bindings, I’m considering what to do next. Should I change channels.feishu.defaultAccount from main to feishu-assistant? I’m unsure because that could affect other agents since the default outgoing account relates to the current assistant.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting configurations and tasks**\\n\\nI'm beginning by verifying configurations and checking the current routing setup to see if further changes are needed after a recent binding change. The user mentioned cleaning up, so I’ll consider writing a note. I also want to ensure that the default account isn't mismatched. Additionally, I might take a look at the Openclaw status and any related bindings. Then, I’ll update the ACTIVE_TASK status with evidence and consider committing it to the workspace.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Deciding on evidence use**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to report on a file, but maybe that’s not necessary. I think I can just reply with the evidence I have. I'm wondering if I should use memory_search, but it might be better to rely on the current context instead. Hm, actually, I think it's best to just execute my plan now without getting too caught up in the details.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"我把这次“路由收口”补做干净：先把当前任务切到执行清单，再核对 `feishu-assistant` 是否还有残留指向 `main`。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_075abb85efaf918e0169c7d98db2ec819a9ce0f2c8c4d36805\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_QfZzicaGKksTIoS0NOf3LR9c|fc_075abb85efaf918e0169c7d99caf0c819aab1fcf112c377218","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 scripts/active_task_cli.py show --path checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":20,"yieldMs":2000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python3 scripts/active_task_cli.py show --path checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\",\"timeout\":20,\"yieldMs\":2000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_InQY1aro