nt date or time, I’m focusing on checking if the \\\"coding-agent\\\" session is active. I also wonder if I can check the status of all agents, particularly to see if the process is running.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Executing status check for coding agent**\\n\\nI think I should use `exec` with `openclaw status` alongside `sessions --all-agents --json` to filter for the \\\"coding-agent\\\" and see if it’s active. However, the developer mentions that I shouldn't narrate low-risk tool calls, so I’ll focus on the tool call itself. I wonder if I need to access today's memory, but that might not be necessary. I can also consider using `multi_tool_use.parallel` for checking the status and listing sessions together.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_DwGWs96OcQfRsE3TJVAFaVPF|fc_075abb85efaf918e0169c7febc4378819a9fd914ae5e9efb96","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status | sed -n '1,180p'","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":60,"yieldMs":4000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw status | sed -n '1,180p'\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\",\"timeout\":60,\"yieldMs\":4000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Svf8MeJ13GqDxlzwY57PzOv3|fc_075abb85efaf918e0169c7febc43ac819aae4e8025213c48a9","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"activeMinutes":360,"limit":200,"messageLimit":1},"partialJson":"{\"activeMinutes\":360,\"limit\":200,\"messageLimit\":1}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_D4MN4XA50GZdTVcqnjFmfFbr|fc_075abb85efaf918e0169c7febc43bc819a986dd0c264725059","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw sessions --all-agents --json | python3 - <<'PY'\nimport sys, json\narr=json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor s in arr:\n    if 'coding-agent' in (s.get('key','')) or s.get('deliveryContext',{}).get('accountId')=='coding-agent':\n        print(json.dumps(s, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\nPY","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":80,"yieldMs":6000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw sessions --all-agents --json |